it's just a critique
of the PDF viewers.

01:28:06.694 --> 01:28:09.670
So if you have a PDF viewer that
can scroll, which many

01:28:09.670 --> 01:28:11.654
can, you could actually
use that.

01:28:11.654 --> 01:28:15.126
The problem is that screens
are not big enough.

01:28:15.126 --> 01:28:17.110
That's really the fundamental
issue.

01:28:21.574 --> 01:28:26.286
So if this slide is taking up
the entire screen space, when

01:28:26.286 --> 01:28:30.998
you scroll it, stuff goes off
these screens, and gets

01:28:30.998 --> 01:28:32.060
replaced by new stuff.

01:28:32.060 --> 01:28:35.050
So that problem is really
hard to work around.

01:28:35.050 --> 01:28:37.390
What you really need is multiple
screens, and multiple

01:28:37.390 --> 01:28:38.640
projectors.

01:28:41.760 --> 01:28:44.250
Many questions asked, what do
you do if you're in a room

01:28:44.250 --> 01:28:46.332
